Phyloseq objects

# Taxa
tax <- ko %>%
  select(-KO_definition) %>% 
  tax_table(as.matrix(.)) %>% 
  'taxa_names<-'(.[, "ta1"])

NMR

# Sample table
sample_nmr <- nmr_metadata %>% 
  base::transform(gtools::mixedorder(rownames(.))) %>% 
  mutate(tissue = NULL, #remove tissue column
         model = rep("nmr"), #create model column
         sample = paste(.$id, .$origin, .$animal)) %>% #create sample column
  'rownames<-'(.$sample) %>% #set ID as rownames
  sample_data()

# OTU table
otu_nmr <- nmr_raw %>% 
  'rownames<-'(.$KO) %>% #set M number as rownames
  'colnames<-'(sub("D", "N", colnames(.))) %>% #adjust ID for NMR
  select_if(is.numeric) %>% #remove character cols
  select_if(colnames(.) %in% nmr_metadata$id) %>% #only rarefied samples
  filter(rowSums(.)!=0) %>%
  select(gtools::mixedorder(colnames(.))) %>%
  'colnames<-'(sample_nmr$sample) %>% #sample as rownames
  otu_table(., taxa_are_rows = TRUE) #create otu table

sample_names(sample_nmr) == sample_names(otu_nmr)
## [1] TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE
# PS object
ps_nmr <- merge_phyloseq(otu_nmr,
                         tax,
                         sample_nmr)

Mice

# Sample table
mice_meta <- mice_metadata %>% 
  base::transform(gtools::mixedorder(rownames(.))) %>% 
  mutate(model = rep("mouse"), #create model column
         sample = paste(.$id, .$origin, .$animal)) %>% #create sample column
  'rownames<-'(.$sample) #set ID as rownames
 
sample_mice <- sample_data(mice_meta)

# OTU table
modules_mice <- mice_raw %>% 
  left_join(poo_raw, by = "KO") %>% 
  mutate_all(funs(ifelse(is.na(.), 0, .))) %>% 
  'rownames<-'(.$KO) %>% #set KO number as rownames
  select_if(is.numeric) %>% #remove character cols
  'colnames<-'(sub(".", "M", colnames(.))) %>% #adjust ID for mice
  select_if(colnames(.) %in% mice_metadata$id) %>% 
  filter(rowSums(.)!=0) %>%
  select(gtools::mixedorder(colnames(.))) %>%
  'colnames<-'(sample_mice$sample) #sample as rownames

otu_mice <- otu_table(modules_mice, taxa_are_rows = TRUE) #create otu table

sample_names(sample_mice) == sample_names(otu_mice)
##  [1] TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE
## [16] TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE TRUE
# PS object
ps_mice <- merge_phyloseq(otu_mice,
                          tax,
                          sample_mice)

# Check for near zero variance (would give correlation where there is none)
nzv_nmr <- caret::nearZeroVar(ps_nmr %>% 
                     otu_table() %>% 
                     t(),freqCut = 8/1, #(number of variables-1)/1
                     uniqueCut = 10, saveMetrics = TRUE)

# Removes non-zero predictors
ps_nzv_nmr <- prune_taxa(nzv_nmr[nzv_nmr[,"nzv"] == 0, ] %>%
                               rownames() %>%
                               as.character(),
                               ps_nmr)

# Create pairs for stat tests between alpha div
path_nmr <- levels(factor(sample_data(ps_nzv_nmr)$origin)) # get the variables
path_pairs_nmr <- combn(seq_along(path_nmr), 2, simplify = FALSE, FUN = function(i)path_nmr[i]) #creates all possible pairs

# Compute alpha diversity
alpha_nmr <- microbiome::alpha(ps_nzv_nmr, index = c('shannon', 'observed')) # Shannon (and package) most accurate

Alpha diversity

# Check for near zero variance (would give correlation where there is none)
nzv_mice <- caret::nearZeroVar(ps_mice %>% 
                     otu_table() %>% 
                     t(),freqCut = 17/1, #(number of variables-1)/1
                     uniqueCut = 10, saveMetrics = TRUE)

# Removes non-zero predictors
ps_nzv_mice <- phyloseq::prune_taxa(nzv_mice[nzv_mice[,"nzv"] == 0, ] %>%
                               rownames() %>%
                               as.character(),
                               ps_mice)

# Create pairs for stat tests between alpha div
path_mice <- levels(factor(sample_data(ps_nzv_mice)$origin)) # get the variables
path_pairs_mice <- combn(seq_along(path_mice), 2, simplify = FALSE, FUN = function(i)path_mice[i]) #creates all possible pairs

# Compute alpha diversity
alpha_mice <- microbiome::alpha(ps_nzv_mice, index = c('shannon', 'observed')) # Shannon (and package) most accurate
head(alpha_mice)

# Add origin column
alpha_mice$origin <- factor(sample_data(ps_nzv_mice)$origin, levels = c("si1", "si2", "si3", "caecum", "colon", "stool"))

# Add SI/LI/stool
alpha_mice <- alpha_mice %>% 
  mutate(region = case_when(origin == "si1"  ~ "SI",
                             origin == "si2" ~ "SI", 
                             origin == "si3" ~ "SI",
                             origin == "caecum" ~ "LI", 
                             origin == "colon" ~ "LI",
                             origin == "stool" ~ "stool"))
